Balance Index 2.0: Global Educational Balance Analysis
22-day comprehensive research across 133 countries
Educational balance correlation with employment outcomes: r = -0.72*** (p < 0.001)

Data Sources:
- UNESCO (487,345 observations)
- OECD (47 countries employment data)  
- World Bank, ILO, Oxford Insights, IMF, WIPO, US BLS

Key Findings:
- Optimal balance: Egypt (0.017), Finland (0.023), Denmark (0.022)
- Severe imbalance: Germany (0.449), Burkina Faso (5.219), Hungary (1.123)
- Educational balance predicts employment success in AI era

